		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=298986"><span id="Scholar">Felicite</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="100" width="100" src="/uf/Felicite/avatar100.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />67 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Felicite&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>The &quot;surefire&quot; way to recharge it used to be so called vendor recharging. <br /> <br />Sell a staff with 10 charges to an empty vendor.. then sell a staff with no charges to the same vendor.&nbsp;&nbsp;The second staff would &quot;combine&quot; in the vendor's inventory and you would be able to buy back two of the staffs, both with 10 charges. <br /> <br />(ok.. I admit I am old and tired.. it could be you sold the no charge first, then the 10 charge.. but.. ragging me on that is moot because..) <br /> <br />SOE has totally removed this facility from the game.  When you sell items that have charges to a vendor, it tracks each unique count of charges as a unique item.  In the example above.. you would see two Staff of Forbidden Rites in the vendors inventory.. one with 10 charges, one with none. <br /> <br />Beyond bribing a GM, there is no way to recharge this item.  Start building a team of 50 alts to farm them.. it's what many guilds do. <br /> <br />The item that can be recharged with a PoK quest is &quot;Mystic Cloak&quot; ( <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2258" title="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2258" target="akztarg">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2258</a> ).. because of this quest it's like an urban legend that just about every other item with charges &quot;can be recharged.. there is some quest on the PoK.</p>
