<p>Yeah. But I don't think it's because the item has been removed from the drop table (can you think of any reason why the would remove it?). If you note all the posts, they never say: &quot;We've killed Vox X number of times over the last Y months and never gotten a drop&quot;. They all say &quot;We've been raiding naggy/vox for X months and haven't seen one drop&quot;. Ok. There was one post providing second hand information about a server(?) killing Vox every week&nbsp;&nbsp;and not seeing one since oct 2002 (I'm assuming a regular open raid kill process on that server). That post is immediately followed by another saying they got three in 2003. <br /> <br /> <br />My assumption is that most people who do naggy/vox kill naggy many many times more often then vox. Naggy's easier. I don't know of any guilds that actually schedule and organize kills on those dragons anymore, so most raids are going to be pickup/open raids. It's many times easier to kill naggy then vox with groups like that, so I'm betting that most of the time, the raid kills naggy, then fails a few times on vox and gives up. <br /> <br />End result is that vox loot rarely shows up, so this staff drops maybe a couple times a year on most servers. <br /> <br />It could be that it's been removed, but I just find that unlikely.</p>
